data.name: MD_ExtendedElementInformation_parentEntity

data.name: MD_ExtendedElementInformation_rationale

data.name: MD_ExtendedElementInformation_rule

data.name: MD_ExtendedElementInformation_shortName

data.name: MD_FeatureCatalogueDescription
data.value: Identifies the feature catalogue or the conceptual schema associated with the resource. Data type: MD_FeatureCatalogueDescription. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_FeatureCatalogueDescription_complianceCode
data.value: Indicates whether the cited feature catalogue complies with ISO 19110. Data type: Boolean. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_FeatureCatalogueDescription_featureCatalogueCitation
data.value: A citation that identifies an external feature catalogue. Data type: CI_Citation. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_FeatureCatalogueDescription_featureTypes

data.name: MD_FeatureCatalogueDescription_includedWithDataset

data.name: MD_FeatureCatalogueDescription_language

data.name: MD_Format_amendmentNumber

data.name: MD_Format_fileDecompressionTechnique
data.value: The algorithms or processes that must be applied to read or expand the distributed resource, if it was compressed. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Format_formatDistirbutor

data.name: MD_Format_name

data.name: MD_Format_specification

data.name: MD_Format_version

data.name: MD_GeometricObjects_geometricObjectCount
data.value: The total number of the given type of objects in the dataset. Data type: Integer greater than zero. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_GeometricObjects_geometricObjectType
data.value: Identifies a type of object that occurs in the dataset. These may be zero-, one-, two-, or three-dimensional objects. Data type: MD_GeometricObjectTypeCode. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Georectified
data.value: Describes raster data with regularly-spaced cells in a geographic or projected coordinate system such that any cell can be geolocated given its grid coordinate, the grid origin, cell spacing, and orientation. Data type: MD_Georectified. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Georectified_centerPoint
data.value: The location in the raster's coordinate system of the cell halfway between opposite ends of the raster in its horizontal dimensions. Data type: GM_Point. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Georectified_checkPointAvailability
data.value: Indicates if a collection of well-known positions on the ground are available to test the accuracy of the georeferenced raster data. Data type: Boolean. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Georectified_checkPointDescription
data.value: Describes the geographic position points used to test the accuracy of the georeferenced raster data. A description must be provided if check points are available. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Georectified_cornerPoints
data.value: The locations in the raster's coordinate system of the cells at opposite ends of two diagonals in the raster's horizontal dimensions. There are four corner points in a georectified raster—at least two corner points along one diagonal are required. The first corner point corresponds to the raster's origin. Data type: GM_Point. From: ISO 19115:2003/Cor. 1:2006.

data.name: MD_Georectified_pointInPixel
data.value: The location within a raster cell that corresponds to the Earth location for that cell. Data type: MD_PixelOrientationCode. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Georectified_transformationDimensionDescription
data.value: Describes the transformation that was performed to georectify the raster. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Georectified_transformationDimensionMapping
data.value: Identifies which of the raster's axes contain information about the horizontal spatial dimensions. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Georeferenceable
data.value: Raster data with irregularly spaced cells such that individual cells can be geolocated using geolocation information provided with the data, but cannot be geolocated using the grid properties alone. Data type: MD_Georeferenceable. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Georeferenceable_controlPointAvailability
data.value: Indicates whether control points are available. Data type: Boolean. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Georeferenceable_georeferencedParameters
data.value: Describes the parameters that support georeferencing for the raster data. Data type: Record. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Georeferenceable_orientationParameterAvailability
data.value: Indicates whether orientation parameters are available. Data type: Boolean. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Georeferenceable_orientationparameterDescription
data.value: Describes the parameters that in turn describe a sensor's orientation. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Georeferenceable_parameterCitation
data.value: A citation identifying a document that describes the georeferencing parameters for the raster data. Data type: CI_Citation. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_GridSpatialRepresentation
data.value: Information describing raster data. Data type: MD_GridSpatialRepresentation. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_GridSpatialRepresentation_axisDimensionProperties
data.value: Describes the spatial and temporal axes of the data. Data type: MD_Dimension. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_GridSpatialRepresentation_cellGeometry
data.value: Indicates if raster cells are managed as points or areas. Data type: MD_CellGeometryCode. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_GridSpatialRepresentation_numberOfDimensions
data.value: The number of independent spatial and temporal axes represented in the data. Data type: Integer. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_GridSpatialRepresentation_transformationParameterAvailability
data.value: Indicates whether parameters for transforming between image coordinates and geographic or map coordinates are available. Data type: Boolean. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Identification_abstract
data.value: A brief narrative summary of the resource's content. In metadata standards this information is known as the abstract. ArcGIS Online refers to this information as the resource's description. For geoprocessing tools this information is referred to as the tool's summary. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115.

data.name: MD_Identification_aggregationInfo
data.value: Description of a related resource, or an aggregation of resources in which this resource participates. Data type: MD_AggregateInformation. From: ISO 19115.

data.name: MD_Identification_citation
data.value: The citation for the resource. Data type: CI_Citation. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Identification_credit
data.value: A recognition of those who created or contributed to the resource. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115.

data.name: MD_Identification_graphicOverview
data.value: An external graphic file that illustrates the resource's content. If a map is pictured, its legend should be included. A graphic overview is especially useful when the referenced file is available on the Internet and can be accessed with a URL or a similar online address; a graphic like this will be available when metadata is published outside of ArcGIS. In contrast, a thumbnail is a small graphic that is embedded within the item's metadata; ArcGIS software can decode and display the thumbnail, but other software might not include that capability. Data type: MD_BrowseGraphic. From: ISO 19115.

data.name: MD_Identification_pointOfContact
data.value: Identifies a person or organization associated with the resource. Data type: CI_ResponsibleParty. From: ISO 19115.

data.name: MD_Identification_purpose
data.value: A summary of the intentions with which the resource was developed. In metadata standards this information is known as the purpose. ArcGIS Online refers to this information as the resource's summary. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115.

data.name: MD_Identification_resourceConstraints
data.value: Describes restrictions on accessing and using the resource. Data type: MD_Constraints. From: ISO 19115.

data.name: MD_Identification_resourceFormat
data.value: A description of the resource's format. Data type: MD_Format. From: ISO 19115.

data.name: MD_Identification_resourceMaintenance
data.value: Describes the frequency of updates to the resource and the scope of those changes. Data type: MD_MaintenanceInformation. From: ISO 19115.

data.name: MD_Identification_resourceSpecificUsage
data.value: Basic information about how the resource is used. Data type: MD_Usage. From: ISO 19115.

data.name: MD_DataIdentification_spatialRepresentationType
data.value: Identifies the method used to spatially represent geographic information. Data type: MD_SpatialRepresentationTypeCode. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Identification_status
data.value: The status of the resource. Data type: MD_ProgressCode. From: ISO 19115.

data.name: MD_Identifier_authority
data.value: A citation that identifies the reference documenting the details associated with the coded value, or the person or organization responsible for maintaining the namespace that uniquely identifies the code. For example, if the code identifies an EPSG-defined spatial reference the authority would identify an EPSG-produced reference providing complete details about that spatial reference. Data type: CI_Citation. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Identifier_code
data.value: An alphanumeric value that identifies an authoritative reference, or an instance in a namespace. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ImageDescription
data.value: For rasters that are images, provides detailed information that may affect their suitability for use. Data type: MD_ImageDescription. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ImageDescription_cameraCalibrationInformationAvailability
data.value: Indicates whether information is available for camera calibration corrections. Data type: Boolean. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ImageDescription_cloudCoverPercentage
data.value: Describes the area of the image that is obscured by clouds, expressed as a percentage of the image's horizontal extent. Data type: Real numbers between 0.0 and 100.0. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ImageDescription_compressionGenerationQuantity
data.value: The total number of lossy compression cycles that have been performed on the image. Data type: Integer. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ImageDescription_filmDistortionInformationAvailability
data.value: Indicates whether Calibration Reseau information is available. Data type: Boolean. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ImageDescription_illuminationAzimuthAngle
data.value: The illumination azimuth measured in degrees clockwise from true North at the time the image is taken. For images from a scanning device, refer to the centre pixel of the image. Data type: Real numbers between 0.0 and 360.0. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ImageDescription_illuminationElevationAngle
data.value: The illumination elevation, measured in degrees clockwise from the target plane at intersection of the optical line of sight with the Earth’s surface. For images from a scanning device, refer to the centre pixel of the image. Data type: Real numbers between -90.0 and 90.0. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ImageDescription_imageQualityCode
data.value: Identifies the image quality. Data type: MD_Identifier. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ImageDescription_imagingCondition
data.value: Identifies a condition that affects the image quality. Data type: MD_ImagingConditionCode. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ImageDescription_lensDistortionInformationAvailability
data.value: Indicates whether lens aberration correction information is available. Data type: Boolean. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ImageDescription_processingLevelCode
data.value: A code provided by the image distributor identifying the level of radiometric and geometric processing performed on the data. Data type: MD_Identifier. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ImageDescription_radiometricCalibrationDataAvailability
data.value: Indicates whether information is available for generating a radiometrically calibrated image. Data type: Boolean. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ImageDescription_triangulationIndicator
data.value: Indicates whether triangulation has been performed on the image. Data type: Boolean. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Keywords_discipline
data.value: Keywords that associate the resource with a branch of instruction or specialized learning. Data type: MD_Keywords, MD_KeywordTypeCode=discipline. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Keywords_keyword
data.value: A commonly used word or a formal term or phrase that describes the resource. Place each keyword on a separate line. A keyword can be a phrase that includes a comma or other punctuation. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115

data.name: MD_Keywords_other
data.value: Keywords that don't fit into other categories that describe characteristics of the resource, but which may be derived from a thesaurus. Data type: MD_Keywords; no associated MD_KeywordTypeCode. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Keywords_place
data.value: Keywords that associate the resource with a location. Data type: MD_Keywords, MD_KeywordTypeCode=place. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Keywords_stratum
data.value: Keywords that associate the resource with a layer or level, for example, in the soil, sea, or atmosphere. Data type: MD_Keywords, MD_KeywordTypeCode=stratum. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Keywords_temporal
data.value: Keywords that associate the resource with a time period. Data type: MD_Keywords, MD_KeywordTypeCode=temporal. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Keywords_theme
data.value: Keywords that associate the resource with a particular subject or topic. Data type: MD_Keywords, MD_KeywordTypeCode=theme. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Keywords_thesaurusName
data.value: Identifies a formally registered thesaurus or an authoritative source from which the keywords were derived. Data type: CI_Citation. From: ISO 19115.

data.name: MD_LegalConstraints_accessConstraints
data.value: Restrictions or limitations on obtaining the resource or metadata; for example, to assure the protection of privacy or intellectual property. Data type: MD_RestrictionCode. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_LegalConstraints_otherConstraints
data.value: Other restrictions and legal prerequisites for accessing and using the resource or metadata. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_LegalConstraints_useConstraints
data.value: Restrictions, limitations, or warnings on using the resource or metadata; for example, to assure the protection of privacy or intellectual property. Data type: MD_RestrictionCode. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_MaintenanceInformation_contact
data.value: The person or organization who maintains the resource or metadata. Data type: CI_ResponsibleParty. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_MaintenanceInformation_dateOfNextUpdate
data.value: The scheduled revision date. Data type: Date. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_MaintenanceInformation_maintenanceAndUpdateFrequency
data.value: The frequency with which the resource or metadata is updated. Data type: MD_MaintenanceFrequencyCode. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_MaintenanceInformation_maintenanceNote
data.value: Describes the specific requirements for maintaining the resource. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_MaintenanceInformation_updateScope
data.value: The scope of data for which this maintenance information applies. Data type: MD_ScopeCode. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_MaintenanceInformation_updateScopeDescription
data.value: Provides additional information describing the range or extent of the updates. Data type: MD_ScopeDescription. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_MaintenanceInformation_userDefinedMaintenanceFrequency
data.value: Describes a custom maintenance period as the duration of time between updates. Durations are formatted as PnYnMnDTnHnMnS, where the length of time is nY years, nM months, nD days, nH hours, nM minutes, and nS seconds. The period designator, "P", must be provided. The date/time separator, "T", must be present when units of time are given and must be absent when units of time are omitted. Units in the duration that are zero can be omitted. At least one number and its designator must be provided. Seconds may have a decimal fraction. For example, a period of 45 days would be P45D. Data type: TM_PeriodDuration. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Medium_density
data.value: The density at which the data is recorded. Data type: Real numbers greater than 0.0. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Medium_densityUnits
data.value: The units of measure for the recording density. Units must are required if a density has been provided. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Medium_mediumFormat
data.value: The method used to write data to the medium. Data type: MD_MediumFormatCode. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Medium_mediumNote
data.value: Describes any limitations or requirements for using the medium. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Medium_name
data.value: The name of the medium on which the resource can be received. Data type: MD_MediumNameCode. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Medium_volumes
data.value: The number of items in the media identified. Data type: Integer numbers greater than 0. From: ISO 19115:2003/ Cor. 1:2006.

data.name: MD_Metadata
data.value: Metadata describes a resource or set of resources. Data type: MD_Metadata. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_MetadataExtensionInformation_extendedElementInformation
data.value: Describes metadata elements not included in ISO 19115 that are required to describe geographic resources. Data type: MD_ExtendedElementInformation. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_MetadataExtensionInformation_extensionOnLineResource
data.value: Provides online information about the community profile name and the modifications it makes to the standard metadata elements. Data type: CI_OnlineResource. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Metadata_applicationSchemaInfo
data.value: Information about the conceptual schema used to build the resource's data. Data type: MD_ApplicationSchemaInformation. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Metadata_characterSet
data.value: The character encoding used for the metadata. ArcGIS metadata is encoded as UTF-8. Data type: MD_CharacterSetCode. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Metadata_contact
data.value: The person or organization responsible for the metadata. Data type: CI_ResponsibleParty. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Metadata_contentInfo
data.value: Information about a feature catalogue used by the resource's vector data, and a description of the resource's raster or image data characteristics. Data type: MD_ContentInformation. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Metadata_dataQualityInfo
data.value: An assessment of the resource's quality. Data type: DQ_DataQuality. From: ISO 19115.

data.name: MD_Metadata_dataSetURI
data.value: The Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) of the resource described by the metadata. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Metadata_dateStamp
data.value: The date when the metadata was created or updated. Data type: Date. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Metadata_distributionInfo
data.value: Information about the distributor of and options for obtaining the resource. Data type: MD_DistributionInformation. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Metadata_fileIdentifier
data.value: A unique identifier for the metadata. An identifier generated by ArcGIS is typically a Globally Unique Identifier (GUID). Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Metadata_hierarchyLevel
data.value: The hierarchical scope to which the metadata applies. For example, the hierarchy of resources might consist of a service that provides access to a map that accesses several datasets. This information is required if the resource's hierarchy level is a level other than "dataset". Data type: MD_ScopeCode. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Metadata_hierarchyLevelName
data.value: The name of the hierarchy level for which the metadata is provided. This information is required if the resource's hierarchy level is a level other than "dataset". Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Metadata_language
data.value: The primary language of information provided in the metadata. This information is required because the UTF-8 encoding used by ArcGIS does not restrict the metadata to a specific language. Data type: ISO 639 language codes. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Metadata_metadataConstraints
data.value: Describes restrictions on accessing and using the metadata. Data type: MD_Constraints. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Metadata_metadataExtensionInfo
data.value: Description of extensions to the metadata standard or profile that are used in the metadata. Data type: MD_MetadataExtensionInformation. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Metadata_metadataMaintenance
data.value: Describes the frequency of metadata updates and the scope of those changes. Data type: MD_MaintenanceInformation. From: ISO 19115.

data.name: MD_Metadata_metadataStandardName
data.value: The name of the metadata standard used. Also, the name of the metadata profile used, if appropriate. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Metadata_metadataStandardVersion
data.value: The version of the metadata standard used. Also, the version of the metadata profile used, if appropriate. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003/Cor. 1:2006.

data.name: MD_Metadata_parentIdentifier
data.value: Unique identifier of the "parent" metadata to which this metadata is a subset, or "child". For example, if the metadata describes a resource that is part of a series, the parent metadata would describe the series as a whole. This information is required if there is an upper hierarchy level resource of which this resource is a part. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003/Cor. 1:2006.

data.name: MD_Metadata_portrayalCatalogueInfo
data.value: Information about the catalogue of rules defined for portraying the resource. Data type: MD_PortrayalCatalogueReference. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Metadata_referenceSystemInfo
data.value: Description of the spatial and temporal reference systems used in the resource. Data type: MD_ReferenceSystem. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Metadata_spatialRepresentationInfo
data.value: Description of the digital representation of the resource's spatial information. Data type: MD_SpatialRepresentation. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_PortrayalCatalogueReference_portrayalCatalogueCitation
data.value: A citation that identifies a portrayal catalogue. Data type: CI_Citation. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_RangeDimension
data.value: Describes the range of cell values for each raster dimension. Data type: MD_RangeDimension. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_RangeDimensions_descriptor
data.value: Describes the range of values possible for this set of cells. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_RangeDimension_sequenceIdentifier
data.value: A number that uniquely identifies instances of bands of wavelengths on which a sensor operates. Data type: MemberName. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ReferenceSystem_referenceSystemIdentifier
data.value: Identifies the resource's spatial reference. Data type: RS_Identifier. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_RepresentativeFraction_denominator
data.value: The number below the line in a vulgar fraction. For example, if the scale is 1:24000, the denominator would be 24000. Data type: Integer greater than zero. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Resolution_distance
data.value: The level of detail provided by the resource, expressed as the ground sample distance. Data type: Distance. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Resolution_equivalentScale
data.value: The level of detail provided by the resource, expressed as the scale of a comparable hardcopy map or chart. Data type: MD_RepresentativeFraction. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ScopeDescription_attributeInstances
data.value: Identifies the attribute instances to which the information applies. Data type: GF_AttributeType. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ScopeDescription_attributes
data.value: Identifies the instances of attribute types to which the information applies. Data type: GF_AttributeType. From: ISO 19115:2003/Cor. 1:2006.

data.name: MD_ScopeDescription_dataset
data.value: Identifies the dataset to which the information applies. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ScopeDescription_featureInstances
data.value: Identifies the feature instances to which the information applies. Data type: GF_AttributeType. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_ScopeDescription_features
data.value: Identifies instances of feature types to which the information applies. Data type: GF_AttributeType. From: ISO 19115:2003/Cor. 1:2006.

data.name: MD_ScopeDescription_other
data.value: Identifies another class of information to which the information applies. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_SecurityConstraints_classification
data.value: Identifies any handling restrictions on the resource or metadata. Data type: MD_ClassificationCode. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_SecurityConstraints_classificationSystem
data.value: The name of the classification system. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_SecurityConstraints_handlingDescription
data.value: Provides additional information about the restrictions on handling the resource or metadata. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_SecurityConstraints_userNote
data.value: Explains any legal or other restrictions and prerequisites for obtaining and using the resource or metadata. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_StandardOrderProcess_fees
data.value: Describes any fees and terms for obtaining the resource. Fees should include monetary units as specified in ISO 4217. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_StandardOrderProcess_orderingInstructions
data.value: Describes instructions, terms, and services provided by the distributor. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_StandardOrderProcess_plannedAvailableDateTime
data.value: The date and time when the resource will be available. Data type: DateTime. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_StandardOrderProcess_turnaround
data.value: Describes the typical period of time in which an order can be fulfilled. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Usage_specificUsage
data.value: A brief description of how the resource was used. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Usage_usageDateTime
data.value: The date and time when the resource was used. Data type: DateTime. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Usage_userContactInfo
data.value: The person or organization who used the resource. Data type: CI_ResponsibleParty. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_Usage_userDeterminedLimitations
data.value: Describes applications determined by the user for which the resource is not suitable. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_VectorSpatialRepresentation
data.value: Describes objects in a vector dataset. Data type: MD_VectorSpatialRepresentation. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_VectorSpatialRepresentation_geometricObjects
data.value: Describes the geometric objects in a vector dataset. Data type: MD_GeometricObjects. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: MD_VectorSpatialRepresentation_topologyLevel
data.value: Identifies the degree of complexity of the spatial relationships between the objects in the dataset. Data type: MD_TopologyLevelCode. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: RS_Identifier_codeSpace
data.value: The name or identifier of the authority responsible for the reference or namespace. For example, if the code identifies an EPSG-defined spatial reference the codespace would be "EPSG". Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: RS_Identifier_version
data.value: The version of the detailed reference associated with the code. For example, if the code identifies an EPSG-defined spatial reference the codespace would be the version number of the EPSG database to which the coded value refers. Data type: CharacterString. From: ISO 19115:2003.

data.name: SV_ServiceIdentification
data.value: Basic information identifying the service described by the metadata, including its capabilities, interfaces, and behaviors. Data type: SV_ServiceIdentification. From: ISO 19119:2005/Amd. 1:2008.

data.name: MD_Metadata_locale
data.value: Identifies additional locales in which information is provided to describe the resource.
